Preheat your oven to 200°C. Chop the @sweet potato{2} into wedges about 1cm wide (no need
to peel!). Put them on a lined #baking tray{} and drizzle over some oil. Season with a
pinch of @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}. Roast on the top shelf of your oven until
crisp and golden, ~{25-30%minutes}, turn halfway through cooking.

Halve, peel and chop the @echalion shallot{1} into ½cm pieces. Halve the @cherry plum
tomatoes{200}. Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1}(peeled and grated). Slice the
@feta cheese{100} into six long rectangles. Drain and rinse the @lentils{1%can} in a
#sieve{}.

Lay some foil on another baking tray and pop the tomatoes on one half. Drizzle over
some oil and season with a pinch of salt and pepper. Put the feta slices on the other
half and drizzle over some oil. Once the wedges have been in the oven for ~{15%minutes},
put the tomatoes and feta on the middle shelf for the last ~{7-10%minutes} of cooking
time.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of oil in a #frying pan{} on medium heat and add the shallot.
Cook, stirring frequently until soft, ~{4%minutes}. Add the garlic and cook for
~{1%minute} more. Tip the lentils into the pan along with a good pinch of salt and a
grind of pepper. Stir well. Warm the lentils through, ~{3%minutes}, then remove from
the heat.

Squeeze the @lemon{1/2} juice into a #small bowl{} and add the @olive oil{1}. Season
with a pinch of salt and a grind of pepper and whisk together with a #fork{}. Once
the wedges, tomatoes and feta are cooked, remove from the oven. Turn your grill to
high. Add the tomatoes to the lentil mixture along with the lemony dressing. Squeeze
the @honey{15} over the feta and pop under the grill for ~{2%minutes}.

Spoon the garlicky lentils into #bowls{2}. Place your wedges and feta on top (if it
breaks up don't worry, it will still be delicious!) Top with a handful of
@wild rocket{40} and sprinkle over the @pomegranate seeds{80}. Enjoy!

> If you've never honey-roasted your feta before, you're about to take your taste
> buds into the taste stratosphere. Combining golden, creamy feta with lemony
> garlic lentils, earthy sweet potatoes, peppery rocket and fresh pomegranate seeds
> is a flavour combination you're going to love, and one you'll be creating time
> and time again. You can thank us later.